com.storytron.uber

Class Actor

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.storytron.uber.Word
      • com.storytron.uber.Actor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Comparable<Word>

    public final class Actor
extends Word
    Class for representing storyworld characters. An Actor object contains the state needed to represent the situation of a character in a storyworld. This state is described by traits, and certain traits can be added or removed by the author.

    Basically, the Actor class implements a convenient interface for setting and getting the values that define the state, under the assumption that some of this traits can be removed or added from the model.

    Traits which can not be removed are implemented as fields of the class accessed through methods that wrap them. Traits that can be removed or added, are grouped by data type (Text or BNumber) and organized into resizable arrays that hold the trait values. Text trait values are indexed with the type TextTrait, and BNnumber traits are indexed with the type FloatTrait.

    For each Actor FloatTrait that exists in the model (Deikto) there are certain related values in the Actor state.

    • A value for the trait. Manipulated with set(FloatTrait, float) and get(FloatTrait)
    • A value indicating how the Actor perceives the trait on a another Actor. Manipulated with getP(FloatTrait, Actor) and setP(FloatTrait, Actor, Float).
    • A value indicating how sure the Actor is of the value he perceives for the trait on a another Actor. Manipulated with setC(FloatTrait, Actor, Float) and getC(FloatTrait, Actor).
    • A value indicating how the Actor tends to perceive the value of the Trait in other Actors. Represents how optimistic/pessimistic or humble/conceited the Actor is with respect to it. Manipulated with getAccord(FloatTrait) and setAccord(FloatTrait, float)
    • A value indicating how important the trait is to the Actor. Would he discriminate people based on the Trait? Manipulated with getWeight(FloatTrait) and setWeight(FloatTrait, float)
    The Text traits are retrieved through the methods getText(TextTrait) and setText(TextTrait, String).

    For each Stage FloatTrait that exists in the model (Deikto) there are certain related values in the Actor state.

    • A value indicating how the Actor perceives the trait on a given Stage. Manipulated with getP(FloatTrait, Stage) and setP(FloatTrait, Stage, Float).
    • A value indicating how sure the Actor is of the value he perceives for the trait on a Stage. Manipulated with setC(FloatTrait, Stage, Float) and getC(FloatTrait, Stage).
    For each Prop FloatTrait that exists in the model (Deikto) there are certain related values in the Actor state.
    • A value indicating how the Actor perceives the trait on a given Prop. Manipulated with getP(FloatTrait, Prop) and setP(FloatTrait, Prop, Float).
    • A value indicating how sure the Actor is of the value he perceives for the trait on a Prop. Manipulated with setC(FloatTrait, Prop, Float) and getC(FloatTrait, Prop).
    The fixed traits are:
    • active, female, dontMoveMe, unconscious, location, spyingOn, targetStage, occupiedUntil, cBored, howLongToSpy, description. All of them have get an set methods.
    • image: holds in memory an image associated to the actor. Manipulated through the methods getImage(Deikto) and setImage(ScaledImage). It is also possible to retrieve the image as a sequence of png bytes. This is useful for sending the image through the cable. If the image is null the png bytes are obtained from the file on disk.
    • imageFilename: holds the path to an image file associated to the actor. It is manipulated through the methods getImageName() and setImageName(String), but is also set to null when a null image is set using setImage(ScaledImage) (setImage(null)).
    • The elements enumerated in Actor.ExtraTrait. Manipulated with get(com.storytron.uber.Actor.ExtraTrait, Actor) and set(com.storytron.uber.Actor.ExtraTrait, Actor, float)
    • The elements enumerated in Actor.MoodTrait. Manipulated with get(com.storytron.uber.Actor.MoodTrait) and set(com.storytron.uber.Actor.MoodTrait, float).
    Traits can be iterated like shown in the following code snippets. 
      // All non-fixed traits
  for(Trait t:dk.getActorTraits()) {
        zActor.get(t);zActor.set(t,floatValue);
        zActor.getP(t,ofWhom);zActor.setP(t,ofWhom,floatValue);
        zActor.getC(t,ofWhom);zActor.setC(t,ofWhom,floatValue);
        if (t.isVisible()) {
                zActor.getAccord(t);zActor.setAccord(t,floatValue);
                zActor.getWeight(t);zActor.setWeight(t,floatValue);
        }
  }
  for(Trait t:dk.getStageTraits()) {
        zActor.getP(t,ofWhom);zActor.setP(t,ofWhom,floatValue);
        zActor.getC(t,ofWhom);zActor.setC(t,ofWhom,floatValue);
  }
  for(Trait t:dk.getPropTraits()) {
        zActor.getP(t,ofWhom);zActor.setP(t,ofWhom,floatValue);
        zActor.getC(t,ofWhom);zActor.setC(t,ofWhom,floatValue);
  }
  // All moods
  for (MoodTrait t:Actor.MoodTraits) {zActor.get(t);zActor.set(t,floatValue);}
  // All extra traits
  for (ExtraTrait t:Actor.ExtraTraits) {zActor.get(t,ofWhom);zActor.set(t,ofWhom,floatValue);}
